==English==
===Etymology===
Perhaps from Yiddish "hu-ha", an uproar or exclamation of surprise.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-hoo-ha.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''hoo-ha'''
#A [[fuss]], [[uproar]], [[commotion]] or [[stir]]; [[hype]].
#:''There was a big '''hoo-ha''' about it in the papers, and then the world completely forgot the matter.''

